 worry if you do not understand the many terms and figures that we are about to introduce, it takes more than just theoretical assumptions, it requires a fair amount of application as well! Are you ready?\n<h2>Fundamental Analysis</h2>\nJust what is fundamental analysis? To put it simply, fundamental analysis is gaining knowledge about how a company is doing through a few methods. Traders often use a Macro -&gt; Micro method (or a top-down approach) when using fundamental analysis, and that comprises of the economy, industry and company analysis. To be more specific, traders and investors will narrow down their research to suit the present or future economic environment. This means that using a top-down approach will allow you to have better research results according to what you are looking for!\n\nFinancial and annual reports are usually being used as research material when forecasting profits of the company stocks. This will help in getting a basic understanding of the pricing in the stock market.\n\nOne key information that we feel is pertinent is the knowledge of the \'<strong>true value\' </strong>of a stock.<strong> </strong>\n\n<em>\"The market price of a stock tends to move towards its \'intrinsic value\', which is the \'true value\' of a company as calculated by its fundamentals. If the market value does not match the true value of the company, there is an investment opportunity.\" - EuroInvestor </em>\n\nThis means that observing the current market price of a stock and comparing it to the \'true value\' of the company will help in  decision making as well. If the market price is below the \'true value\', traders and investors should buy the stocks because it will be expected to rise and move towards its \'true value\'.','Tip of the Week: How to choose a Stock','','inherit','closed','open','','295-revision-4','','','2013-06-21 15:55:45','2013-06-21 07:55:45','',295,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/295-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(304,4,'2013-06-21 15:57:14',