g stocks is like having children - don\'t get involved with more than you can handle.”\r\n\r\nTradeHero has, hopefully, come to the rescue.\r\n\r\nThat’s all for now – stay tuned for updates!','Welcome to TradeHero’s Official Blog','','inherit','closed','open','','86-revision-8','','','2013-06-20 13:24:53','2013-06-20 05:24:53','',86,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/86-revision-8',0,'revision','',0),(310,4,'2013-06-21 16:00:50','2013-06-21 08:00:50','Many TradeHero users (especially if you\'re new) may ask, <em>I have the application, but I don\'t know how to choose a stock to invest in? How do I go about researching on stocks if no information is given to me? What do the many financial terms in the application mean? I still don\'t know Market Terminology</em>? Fret not, the answers are right here.\n\nWe will be bringing you through a short but succinct guide on <strong>How to choose a Stock</strong>. We will also provide you a list of <strong>Market Terminology</strong> that is essential in your trading journey. (Which is actually found on our <a title=\"FAQ\" href=\"http://www.tradehero.mobi/FAQ\" target=\"_blank\">FAQ</a> page!)\n<h2><strong>How to Choose A Stock:</strong></h2>\nWhen choosing a stock, there are several ways people can choose to analyze, and the two most popular methodologies are <strong>Fundamental Analysis</strong> and <strong>Technical Analysis</strong>.\n\nHaving basic knowledge about the stock market will help in investment decisions. Do not worry if you do not understand the many terms and figures that we are about to introduce, it takes more than just theoretical assumptions, it requires a fair amount of application as well! Are you ready?\n<h2>Fundamental Analysis</h2>\nJust what is fundamental analysis? To put it simply, fundamental analysis is gaining knowledge about how a company is doing through a few methods.\n<ul>\n	<li>Traders often use a Macro -&gt; Micro method (or a top-down approach) when using fundamental analysis, and that  comprises of the economy, industry and company analysis. To be more specific, traders and investors will narrow down their research to suit the present or future economic environment. This means that using a top-down approach will allow you to have better research results according to what you are looking for!</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n	<li>Financial and annual reports are usually being used as research material when forecasting profits of the company stocks. This will help in getting a basic understanding of the pricing in the stock market.</li>\n</ul>\nOne key information that we feel is pertinent is the knowledge of the \'<strong>true value\' </strong>of a stock.<strong> </strong>\n\n<em>\"The market price of a stock tends to move towards its \'intrinsic value\', which is the \'true value\' of a company as calculated by its fundamentals. If the market value does not match the true value of the company, there is an investment opportunity.\" - EuroInvestor </em>\n\nThis means that observing the current market price of a stock and comparing it to the \'true value\' of the company will help in  decision making as well. If the market price is below the \'true value\', traders and investors should buy the stocks because it will be expected to rise and move towards its \'true value\'.\n\nWhat factors then determine the \'true value\'?','Tip of the Week: How to choose a Stock','','inherit','closed','open','','295-revision-9','','','2013-06-21 16:00:50','2013-06-21 08:00:50','',295,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/295-revision-9',0,'revision','',0),(311,4,'2013-06-21 16:15:18','2013-06-21 08:15:18','Many TradeHero users (especially if you\'re new) may ask, <em>I have the application, but I don\'t know how to choose a stock to invest in? How do I go about researching on stocks if no information is given to me? What do the many financial terms in the application mean? I still don\'t know Market Terminology</em>? Fret not, the answers are right here.\n\nWe will be bringing you through a short 