ock: Technical Analysis','','inherit','closed','open','','317-revision','','','2013-06-21 16:52:25','2013-06-21 08:52:25','',317,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/317-revision',0,'revision','',0),(319,4,'2013-06-21 17:17:27','2013-06-21 09:17:27','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tut3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-268\" alt=\"tut3\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tut3.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\n\nIn this tutorial, we will be showing you a step-by-step process on how to Buy and Sell a stock. Although it may seem simple given that the procedures are easy, it takes more than just steps in the trading world. In order to maximise your experience,we suggest looking beyond this tutorial after you grasp a basic understanding of the application.\n<h2><strong>How to Buy/Sell a stock using TradeHero:</strong></h2>\n1. In the buy/sell screen, select a name of the stock. Use the search engine to search for stocks the supported exchanges. You can search by company or symbol name.\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/buysell.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-257\" alt=\"buysell\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/buysell.png\" width=\"354\" height=\"551\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n2.  Use the charts and information provided on the screen to view market data to help you in deciding whether to buy or sell a stock. (T<em>hese information will not be enough, it’s just a guide. You will definitely need more information than that.</em>) Then, use the slider to choose the quantity of stocks that you want to buy. Alternatively, you can use the prefixed amounts found below the slider.\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/APPSTORE3_640x1136_2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-258\" alt=\"APPSTORE3_640x1136_2\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/APPSTORE3_640x1136_2.png\" width=\"360\" height=\"619\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n3. After clicking the Buy button, you can choose to post comments for reasons to buy or sell the stock. You can also choose to share your buy on your social media feeds like Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn. When you’re done, click on Confirm. And there you go, you have just bought yourself a stock!\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-259\" alt=\"image (2)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-2-576x1024.png\" width=\"363\" height=\"645\" /></a>\n\n4.  Similarly, when you want to sell a stock, you can access it through your positions by clicking the middle button and tapping on the <strong>–</strong> button. Then, repeat steps 2 and 3.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBuying and selling a stock isn\'t all that hard once you get the hang of it. Of course, we strongly advise you to do prior research and read up on the actual market before buying or selling a stock. After all, all our data is reflective of the real world and stock market, so why not get more practice to prepare yourself for the real thing? ;)\n\nAnother important function of the application is the <strong>Trade History</strong>.\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-260\" alt=\"image\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-576x1024.png\" width=\"346\" height=\"614\" /></a>\n\nThis screen shows the detailed trade history for a position. You can view the quantity bought or sold, the date and the average price paid after the transaction.\n\n<strong>Realized P&amp;L</strong> is profit or loss banked into your virtual cash after the transaction.\n\n<strong>Unrealised P&amp;L</strong> is the floating profit or loss due to curret market price of the underlying stocks.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong> Stock Alerts</strong>\n\nUsing these information, you will be able to buy and sell a stock on TradeHero easily. Get started! Stay tuned for the last part of our tutorial series, where you will be able to learn <strong>How to Make Real Money</strong> from our application. Til then!\n\n&nbsp;','Tutorial Part Two: Buy and Sell','','inherit','closed','open','','256-revision-14','','','2013-06-21 17:17:27','2013-06-21 09:17:27','',256,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/256-revision-14',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2013-06-24 16:30:34','2013-06-24 08:30:34','','Home-Test','','inherit','closed','open','','320-revision','','','2013-06-24 16:30:34','2013-06-24 08:30:34','',320,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/320-revision',0,'revision','',0),(383,4,'2013-07-31 14:41:37','2013-07-31 06:41:37','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/newsfinaledit.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-406\" alt=\"newsfinaledit\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/newsfinaledit.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\nHello TradeHeroes!\r\n\r\nAs previously mentioned on our <em>Facebook Page (link <a href=\"http://facebook.com/TradeHero\">here</a>)</em>, TradeHero is about to launch a Singapore-based trading competition in early August!(which is really soon!) So, why should you take part in this competition? Well, if you want to stand a chance at winning more than <strong>$30,000</strong> worth of real cash prizes, then you should be a part of this competition! We kid you not, everyone stands an equal chance! Keep looking out for updates here and on our social media platforms, more exciting things are coming soon! Meanwhile, keep practicing and trading!\r\n\r\nThe competition is currently only based in Singapore, but fret not, we\'re looking to offer it to several other countries in the near future!\r\n\r\nIt\'s time to bring out your best trading skills!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/compad2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-384\" alt=\"compad2\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/compad2-692x1024.jpg\" width=\"554\" height=\"819\" /></a>','TradeHero- News & Announcements','','publish','closed','open','','tradehero-news-announcements','','','2013-07-31 14:46:19','2013-07-31 06:46:19','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?p=383',0,'post','',0),(324,1,'2013-06-24 16:30:38','2013-06-24 08:30:38','','Home-Test','','inherit','closed','open','','320-revision-2','','','2013-06-24 16:30:38','2013-06-24 08:30:38','',320,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/320-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(325,1,'2013-06-24 16:34:02','2013-06-24 08:34:02','','Home-Test','','inherit','closed','open','','320-revision-3','','','2013-06-24 16:34:02','2013-06-24 08:34:02','',320,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/320-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(359,4,'2013-07-03 11:23:36','2013-07-03 03:23:36','<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tutr.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-247\" alt=\"tutr\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/tutr.png\" width=\"750\" height=\"250\" /></a>\n\nThis tutorial introduces to you the basic features of TradeHero. If you are a new user, this will be an advisable place to start the ball rolling by understanding what TradeHero is. If you are an existing user, you may also find this tutorial useful as a refresher.\n\nFirstly, what is TradeHero? To cut the story short, we bring TradeHero to you in 3 parts:\n<ul>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Learn to Trade</strong></h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Earn Money</strong></h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Follow Experts</strong></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\nFor more details, refer to our main website at <em>www.tradehero.mobi </em>\n\nTo facilitate better and effective learning, we have broken down the main features into details. By reading through the tutorial, we hope to clarify any doubts concerning the usability of the application, as well as to give an overview of what exactly is happening as you use TradeHero. <!--more-->\n<h2><strong>1. Profile Screen</strong></h2>\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-3.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-250\" alt=\"image (3)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-3.png\" width=\"327\" height=\"580\" /></a>\n\nYour profile screen displays the returns on your portfolio of stocks, the users paying to follow your trades and comments, as well as your performance ranking on different leaderboards.\n\nYou can tap on the center action button to open up more options.\n<ul>\n	<li>The <strong>+ </strong>symbol to   buy shares</li>\n	<li>The <strong>-</strong>  button to sell shares</li>\n	<li>The  <strong>speech</strong>  symbol to post comments. Comments will be sent to your followers and will also appear on your timeline. You are also given options to share your comments on Twitter, Facebook and LinkedIn.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong style=\"font-size: 1.5em;\">2. Community</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/1community.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-229\" alt=\"1community\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/1community.png\" width=\"318\" height=\"402\" /></a>\n\nFind top traders in the leaderboards, ranked either by raw P&amp;L or by our custom Hero quotient ranking algorithm. You can filter by stock exchange, industry sectors, monthly and quarterly returns and Most Skilled traders.\n\nAlso, you can compete with your friends on the Friends Leaderboard. How so? By connecting accounts from Facebook, Twitter and LinkedIn to see how you stack up amongst your friends.\n<h2><strong>3. Portfolio</strong></h2>\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/position.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-232\" alt=\"position\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/position.png\" width=\"320\" height=\"496\" /></a>\n\nThis screen details your current portfolio of stocks: open positions are shown at the top. Closed positions are displayed below. You can tap on the names of stocks to view more details about your positions. Also, you can tap on the right arrows to see the trade history for each position.\n<h2><strong>4. Followers </strong></h2>\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/followers.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-230\" alt=\"followers\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/followers.jpg\" width=\"328\" height=\"482\" /></a>\n\nThis screen displays the total number of followers and money you earned from them since you joined TradeHero. Drill down each follower’s name to see the revenue history.\n<h2><strong>5. Heroes</strong></h2>\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-5.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-251\" alt=\"image (5)\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/image-5-576x1024.png\" width=\"332\" height=\"590\" /></a>\n\nTo follow a hero, 1 TH credit will be deducted per month. Following a Hero will give you instant push notifications whenever the Hero makes a trade or a comment.\n\nYou will also receive s TradeHero Market Digest email, detailing all the trades and commentary made by the Hero over a weekly or monthly period.\n\nActive heroes are users you are currently following and paying for. Inactive heroes are users that you have stopped paying for.\n<h2><strong>6. Leaderboards</strong></h2>\n<a href=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/Leaderboatd.png\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-231\" alt=\"Leaderboatd\" src=\"http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/Leaderboatd.png\" width=\"328\" height=\"552\" /></a>\n\nLeaderboards rank the performance of individual users worldwide, make more trades and fight to reach the top of the leaderboard to gain followers!\n\nTo expand your options, you can tap on the names of the users. You can also view the user’s previous closed positions to find out how he reached his current profit level, but to view the user’s current open positions and receive push notifications when the user makes trades and comments,  you will have to tap Follow User and subscribe to him.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe have just introduced the basic features of TradeHero and what we have to offer. Do look out for our next few tips and tutorials where we will explain more on how to<strong> Buy and Sell shares </strong>on TradeHero, as well as <strong>How to Earn Real Money</strong> using our application. Stay tuned!','Tutorial Part One: Introduction','','inherit','closed','open','','227-revision-23','','','2013-07-03 11:23:36','2013-07-03 03:23:36','',227,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/227-revision-23',0,'revision','',0),(327,1,'2013-06-24 16:34:24','2013-06-24 08:34:24','','Home-Test','','inherit','closed','open','','320-revision-4','','','2013-06-24 16:34:24','2013-06-24 08:34:24','',320,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/320-revision-4',0,'revision','',0),(328,1,'2013-06-24 16:43:58','2013-06-24 08:43:58','Slide 1 - Hello','Slide1','','publish','closed','closed','','slide1','','','2013-06-24 16:43:58','2013-06-24 08:43:58','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?post_type=vp_orbitslides&#038;p=328',0,'vp_orbitslides','',0),(329,1,'2013-06-24 16:44:27','2013-06-24 08:44:27','','923031_10200877358632810_1616242512_n','Take a Position. Trade.','inherit','closed','open','','923031_10200877358632810_1616242512_n','','','2013-06-24 16:44:27','2013-06-24 08:44:27','',328,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/923031_10200877358632810_1616242512_n.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(330,1,'2013-06-24 16:42:48','2013-06-24 08:42:48','','Home-Test','','inherit','closed','open','','320-revision-5','','','2013-06-24 16:42:48','2013-06-24 08:42:48','',320,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/320-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(339,1,'2013-06-24 17:14:36','2013-06-24 09:14:36','','New Slider','','publish','closed','open','','new-slider','','','2013-10-22 17:43:54','2013-10-22 09:43:54','',0,'http://blog.tradehero.mobi/?post_type=ml-slider&#038;p=339',0,'ml-slider','',0),(331,1,'2013-06-24 16:45:09','2013-06-24 08:45:09','[orbit-slider]','Home-Test','','inherit','closed','open','','320-revision-6','','','2013-06-24 16:45:0